history.content:
Can't speak for the spring course staff, but between the past two semesters (spring and fall) all projects have stayed the same except the last one.

Also, here's a free tip from a former 188 TA: The projects and homeworks exist for you to learn. They aren't going to carry your grade, because almost everyone gets 100% on all of them. Your real grade comes exclusively from the exams, so make sure you actually understand the material. When doing the projects and homework, take notes—write down what misconceptions you had, what lessons you've learned. Bookmark particularly hard problems. Go to section. Do a lot of practice tests. Participate in the contests. Study hard.

Good luck! :)

P.S. When you get to Bayes nets, learn d-separation, even if it isn't required.
